THE REFUSAL of America’s attorney-general, William Barr, to testify before Congress on Thursday is just the latest example of the White House’s stonewalling policy. We look at the constitutional crisis that may be brewing. Facebook moved yesterday to block certain extremists, but this is just one front on which the social-media behemoth is fighting. Mark Zuckerberg’s bid to remake the platform will probably ape its Chinese rival, WeChat. And in Europe, Vietnamese migrants are thriving in some notoriously anti-immigration regions. Runtime: 22 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn